1. What is Juniper Networks?

Juniper Networks is a company that designs and sells networking equipment such as:

Routers

Switches

Firewalls

Security & automation solutions

Juniper is especially known for:

Service provider networks

Data centers

Enterprise networks

2. Junos OS (Core Foundation)

All Juniper devices run Junos OS, which is:

Single OS across all devices

Modular (separate control and forwarding planes)

Highly stable and secure

Key Junos Concepts

Control Plane â€“ Routing protocols, system management

Data (Forwarding) Plane â€“ Packet forwarding

Management Plane â€“ CLI, SSH, NETCONF

3. Juniper Device Types
Routers

MX Series (Service Provider)

PTX Series (Core routing)

SRX (Routing + Security)

Switches

EX Series (Enterprise switching)

QFX Series (Data Center)

Firewalls

SRX Series (Next-Gen Firewall)

4. Junos CLI Basics

Juniper CLI has two main modes:

1. Operational Mode

Used for monitoring and troubleshooting:

show interfaces
show route
show version

2. Configuration Mode

Used to configure devices:

configure
set interfaces ge-0/0/0 unit 0 family inet address 192.168.1.1/24
commit

5. Configuration Hierarchy

Junos uses a hierarchical configuration structure, similar to a tree:

